Nekol Hickey  shared a memory. Kirstie Marie Goforth   ‚ù§ Nekol Hickey November 7, 2015  ¬∑  I've had lots of people say im too nice. That i should have done things differently in situations. Or i shouldn't care about people that have done me wrong once ...  or for years. I know I still get upset often over things. I don't have everything under control. But I've come to a realization recently. What is "too nice?" People "are tired of seeing others walk all over me." I can never change those people. But i can be there for them. I can show them what kindness is. What forgiveness is.  I can't let other people affect who I really am. That would be the real problem. I can't hold onto hurt feelings for very long. And i don't want to. I like that about myself. I've wished i wasn't as sensitive sometimes. Because I let small things hurt me often. But I've grown as a person. Instead of letting that hurt turn to anger I've learned to use it. To understand better, to become more self aware, to be who i want to be. I can look back and see what I would have done in situations....I can see my growth. That alone is so rewarding for me. For anyone that's seen me at my bad times....I'd like to say I want to apologize...But....I didn't know how to be better. For everyone you get mad at....you have to know....those people are doing the best they are capable of. There's an ignorance in everyone. But not everyone wants to be stuck where they are. And anyone willing to be on this path with me. I'm here for you. Always, no matter the past. Life is rough if we choose for it to be. Everyone has their own idea of serenity. I'm not saying this is the right path. But it's the best for me.   See More 12 Comments 1 Share 18 18   Kirstie Marie Goforth and 17 others

description: Kirstie Marie Goforth Six years ago today, I woke up hearing my phone ring early in the morning. I instantly knew something was wrong. I don't know why my mind instantly jumped to something being wrong with Momma, but I knew. The longest, most emotional drive in my life was getting to her. I'm so thankful I had  Jeffrey Matthew Goforth  with me. The roller coaster of emotions I went through for the days, months, and even years afterwards, was nothing I'd ever imagined. He somehow stuck with me through it.  Momma was, and still is, so much of who I am, of my every day life. I imagine I'll always feel that emptiness. Nana and Momma were my world, it feels unnatural to not share our days, these children, our ups and downs, holidays together...   Hold your loved ones close. Life is far too short.
